stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Unclaimed
    Unclaimed --> Claimed: ledger.claim(url, worker_id, ttl)<br/>SET processing_lease:&lt;url&gt; worker_id PX ttl<br/>HSET crawler:processing url url_data<br/>(one Lua script)

    Claimed --> Renewed: ledger.renew(url, worker_id)<br/>GET-compare-PEXPIRE (Lua)
    Renewed --> Claimed

    Claimed --> Released: ledger.release(url, worker_id)<br/>GET-compare-DEL+HDEL (Lua)<br/>returns 1 -> we owned it
    Released --> [*]

    Claimed --> Zombie: ledger.release returns 0<br/>(another worker reclaimed us)
    Zombie --> [*]

    Claimed --> Expired: PEXPIRE fires - worker died<br/>or stalled past ttl
    Expired --> Recovered: another worker calls<br/>ledger.recover_stale()<br/>EXISTS lease == 0 -> HDEL hash<br/>re-enqueue url to frontier
    Recovered --> [*]

    note right of Claimed
        Worker MUST verify_owner(url)
        before any irreversible
        side-effect (Mongo write).
        If verify fails, abort -
        a recovery worker has
        already taken over.
    end note

    note right of Recovered
        Recovery is throttled to
        once per recovery_interval
        (default 10 s) - lease TTL
        bounds the freshness, not
        the recovery loop frequency.
    end note
